{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"feathered-formal-drongo","description":"## Why\nThe compact/delete/init contended-lock tests plant a lock then start a\n`threading.Timer(0.4, unlink)` and assert only `rc == 0` plus snapshot/tombstone presence\n(`tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_compact_index_lock.py:71-85`,\n`tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_delete_init_index_lock.py:83-119`). On a slow runner the\n0.4s timer removes the lock before git's first attempt, so the test passes through the\nordinary success path without ever exercising `_with_index_lock_retry`\n(`gitutil.py:110-129`). VALIDATED.\n\n## What\nSynchronize each test to a confirmed first failure using a barrier or instrumented\n`run_once` seam, and assert the retry actually happened.\n\n## Scope\n- The three contended-lock tests above; add/instrument a seam in the retry loop for tests.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] First attempt deterministically returns the real/simulated `index.lock` error before\n      the lock is released.\n- [ ] Each test asserts at least two attempts occurred (retry path exercised).\n- [ ] Each test asserts a non-lock failure is never retried.\n- [ ] The final event/commit exists; `make test` green.","id":"bdbe-be66-ff34-48dd","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":2,"tags":["p1","concurrency","lock","test-rigor"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Contended index.lock ride-out tests must assert first-failure + retry count"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784810452924001,"uuid":"21d5fd78-84b1-4b74-bf4d-d2c87a5a2850"}